    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Finding Solace</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rosemary Kenah letter on Wendy Lesser's article holds acting has declined and she now watches reruns instead of new episodes of Law and Order (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Over the past couple of years I have hardly watched a current episode of ''Law and Order,'' a show I had recommended over the previous years as the best drama on television. As Wendy Lesser points out, the decline in acting ability was a factor. When the stars can't act, there is a loss in interest in the story.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Over the past couple of years I have hardly watched a current episode of ''Law and Order,'' a show I had recommended over the previous years as the best drama on television. As Wendy Lesser points out, the decline in acting ability was a factor. When the stars can't act, there is a loss in interest in the story.</p>
        <p>When you find something worthwhile on television and you lose it, the only solace is in watching the reruns.</p>
        <p>ROSEMARY KENAH  Whiting, N.J.</p>
        <p>'LAW AND ORDER'</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
